      "writtenOn": "2021-04-19T07:40:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e (note: doesn\u0027t mean we have to change resultdb protos - we can still use a property).\n\nresultdb.settings returns a buildbucket_pb.Builder.ResultDB.\nIs it actually possible to add other field there without modifying the proto file?\n\nFor now, I moved it to\n```\nluci.builder(\n    ...\n    resultdb_settings \u003d ...,\n    test_presentation \u003d resultdb.test_resentation(\n        column_keys \u003d [\"v.gpu\"],\n        grouping_keys \u003d [\"status\", \"v.test_suite\"],\n    ),\n)\n```\n\nAnother confusing thing is that now we have `resultdb.test_presentation`, which sets \"$recipe/milo/test_presentation\".\nAnd we also have `MiloApi.config_test_presentation` that sets \"$recipe/milo/test_presentation\".\nI think we should either put everything under resultdb and set \"$recipe/resultdb/test_presentation\"\nOr put everything under milo and set \"$recipe/milo/test_presentation\".",
      "parentUuid": "73c6061e_565faad4",
      "revId": "3706b0650fa5dd881a316c5443f690f868c50168",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "63420b91_8358ca1c",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/lib/test_presentation.star",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 40,
      "author": {
        "id": 1178685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-16T02:42:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the design doc and in the frontend implementation, this defaults to [\u0027v.test_suite\u0027].\nIn the recipe module, this defaults to [] (by mistake).\n\nBut I\u0027m preferring defaulting to [] now.\nBecause in quite a few places (e.g. protobuf, validate.list), there is no clear distinction between [] and None/undefined.\nWe often needs another field to clearly communicate that the value is set to an empty array rather than left unspecified.\n\nIf we default to [\u0027v.test_suite\u0027], then we\n1. need an extra field to support [] (no extra column), or\n2. force every project to have at least one extra column.\nNeither is good.\n\nThis doesn\u0027t apply to grouping_keys, because forcing them to at least group by status is probably fine.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "3706b0650fa5dd881a316c5443f690f868c50168",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d77bab9e_d4d99064",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/lib/test_presentation.star",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 40,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-16T16:40:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i consider lucicfg a bit more generic codebase than milo and recipes, so I\u0027d prefer it not to hardcode test_suite which is chrome-specific. Chrome-specific star files (that use this func) can define their own defaults.\n\nfrom this perspective, it shouldn\u0027t be a diff between [] and None?",
      "parentUuid": "63420b91_8358ca1c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 31
